<item>
            <title>[LU-13519] expand inode if possible for project quota</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13519</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When upgrading filesystem, it is possible that inode&lt;br/&gt;
 it not big enough to hold project id field, and in that case&lt;br/&gt;
set project ID will return EOVERFLOW error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; Since ldiskfs have the logic to expand inode size automatically,&lt;br/&gt;
 we could add similar logic for project quota.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
